Easiest meal of quarantine. Frittata!! 

The secret is, grill or roast lots of veggies when making your dinner so that you have extra to throw in your frittata. 

The one has zucchini and eggplant roasted from the nights before, topped with some goat cheese. 

If I don’t have milk, I’ll add some sour cream to the eggs to make them nice and fluffy. 

Ps that’s only 3 eggs!!!!

The positivity rate in India has come down for the first time since May. ?
The Covid-19 positivity rate had been on the rise for the past three months, reaching a peak of 9.01 per cent on August 9. The positivity rate began to decline after August 9 and has reached 8.72 per cent in the country now. 
 Positivity rate means the number of people are testing positive out of the total number of tests conducted.

While these are early signs, we can definitely see this as an indication of things coming under control. ?

node.text:
Makassar, Sulawesi, Indonesia • 1996
⁣
En ces temps trouble?s de pande?mie, Kasoar Travel vous emme?ne chaque jour sur les chemins de traverse virtuels. De Sabang a? Merauke (dans le de?sordre et en zigzag), vous parcourrez l'Indone?sie au gre? de nos souvenirs de voyage de 1996 a? aujourd'hui. Et parfois, nous vous convierons a? une e?chappe?e belle vers d'autres contre?es que nous avons eu la chance de visiter.⁣
Selamat jalan… (Bon voyage…)⁣
⁣
During these pandemic's troubled days, Kasoar Travel takes you along to a daily virtual journey. From Sabang to Merauke (without any real order and zigzagging), you will sail across Indonesia following our travels' memories, from 1996 till today. And sometimes, we will invite you to a sweet escape to other countries we had the chance to visit.⁣
Selamat jalan… (Have a nice trip…)⁣
⁣

node.text:
Paid another visit to The Meetball Place. @thatmeetballplace This time sat at the bar and ate our food there. The bar was partitioned with dividers as well which helped with social distancing. 

Food wise we tried a few new items! Tater tots, lobster balls (these were a repeat), lamb balls, and burrata plate. The tater tots had bacon and a horseradish sauce, lamb balls had tzatziki sauce and pita bread and the burrata dish had pesto and roasted tomatoes. All were very delicious and filling. The lobster balls are still my top choice.

node.text:
This was my morning view last week. 
When we realised we'd have to quarantine I thought we'd be fine. During lockdown we generally got on well as a family and it wasn't anywhere near as hard as I thought it would be. But this is day 5 of quarantine and it's pretty un-fun. Everyone is getting on my nerves and I feel like a caged animal. My head feels fuzzy and I'm lethargic. I couldn't figure out why I feel so differently to lockdown. But today it has dawned on me what the one major difference is. During lockdown we did a long dog walk daily. Now I know the benefits of exercise on your mental health but I had underestimated just how much that daily walk was helping us all. Being couped up now, unable to walk anywhere, all of us grumpy (mostly me probably), I'm seeing just how much we all need that daily dose of vitamin D and movement. I've always gone on about the importance of movement and getting outdoors and now more than ever I can see how needed it is to remain sane. 
#quarantine #quarantinelife #mentalhealth #movement
